<%= title "How to write an Article that people will read"%>
<p>Showcase your expertise by writing articles on what you know and do. It will help you build a positive reputation, which will increase the public&rsquo;s trust in you and what you offer.</p> <p><strong>A standard article structure:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Summary/Introduction - Tell them what you're going to tell them!</li> <li>Key messages, points &amp; tips - Tell them!</li> <li>Conclusion - Tell them what you've just told them!</li> </ul> <p><strong><span>Other tips:</span></strong></p> <ul> <li>Give vs. promote - Giving and sharing is great for credibility and your knowledge will sell you ... avoid trying to mask a sales pitch as an article.</li> <li><span>Talk about outcomes &amp; processes to get them</span></li> <li><span>Give short examples of case studies</span></li> <li>Be succinct</li> <li>Always spell check</li> <li>Nail it in 900 words or less!</li> <li>Split big subjects up into smaller articles</li> </ul> 
